<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>My answer is based on work in the field of artificial intelligence (usually abbreviated AI) which is the science and engineering of making computers solve problems and behave in ways generally considered to be intelligent.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>However, artificial intelligence is a difficult branch of science and engineering, and, judging by present slow progress, it might take a long time.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>AI research usually involves programming a computer to use specific concepts and to have specific mental qualities.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>From the time of Mendel's experiments with peas to the cracking of the DNA code for proteins, a hundred years elapsed, and genetics isn't done yet.</a>
